      <p>Melatonin takes 30-60 minutes to work. The most important factors for fast, reliable onset are: choosing the right form (liquid or gummies), taking it 30-60 minutes before bed (not at bedtime), avoiding screens and bright light after ingestion, using an evidence-based dose of 0.5-3mg, and being consistent every night. Higher doses do not work faster and may actually impair sleep quality through receptor desensitization.</p>
